      {
        "heading": "Brazilian Style",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tip",
            "text": "Brazilians often shorten 'está' to 'tá' in casual speech: 'Tá calor!' (It's hot!)"
          },
          {
            "type": "tip",
            "text": "In Brazil, you say 'Está chovendo' (gerund). In Portugal, it's 'Está a chover'."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Brazilian Climate",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tip",
            "text": "Most of Brazil has tropical weather. Snow is rare and only occurs in the southern states."
          },
          {
            "type": "example",
            "source": "Vai fazer muito calor amanhã",
            "target": "It's going to be very hot tomorrow",
            "note": "Common in Brazilian weather forecasts"
          }
